Durban - Chatsworth man Kishorlall Hambapesad allegedly caught with R1,3 million worth of drugs was denied bail for the second time in the Chatsworth Magistrate's Court on Monday. Hambapesad, 45, presented new facts for his bail application. He was represented by Durban Advocate Willie Lombard. On September 16, Hambapapersad and Mozambican national Lucas Mashaba, 21, were arrested in Golden Poppy Street in Crossmoor, Chatsworth. Police confiscated 22 200 heroin capsules, 2 826 pieces of rock cocaine and 505 mandrax tablets with an estimated street value of R1.3 million. Mashaba abandoned his bail application. According to KwaZulu Natal police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane the arrest was a joint operation between Provincial Organised Crime Unit, Provincial Drug Unit, and Umlazi K9 unit. East Coast Radio reports the KwaZulu-Natal Department of Education is investigating claims that one of two men arrested was the chairperson of a local school governing body. The matter was adjourned to December 19 for further investigation. Daily News